- When surfacing due touches at startup, group by urgency: OVERDUE (past next_touch), DUE TODAY, UPCOMING (next 3 days). For each, show: prospect name, company, deal stage, last touch summary, days since last touch, suggested approach (angle + tone from PATTERNS.md), and why. Format as a scannable table, not paragraphs.
- When surfacing due touches at startup, group by urgency: OVERDUE (past next_touch), DUE TODAY, UPCOMING (next 3 days). For each, show: prospect name, company, deal stage, last touch summary, days since last touch, suggested approach (angle + tone from PATTERNS.md), and why. Format as a scannable table, not paragraphs.
- On deal close (won or lost), fill the Deal Outcome section. This is Loop's most valuable data — it retroactively validates or invalidates every touch in the sequence. For closed-won: deciding factor, what almost killed it, cycle length, final pricing, champion. For closed-lost: why, which objection won, what would be different, where the deal went off track. Immediately update PATTERNS.md deal velocity and objection tables.
