- System pattern retirement rules: (1) Gate STEP (not whole gate) rubber-stamped 20+ times with zero catches → flag step for removal, keep the gate. (2) Smoke check passing 20+ consecutive times → retire to monthly spot-check. (3) CARL LAZY domains: NEVER retire for being dormant — that's their design. Only flag if a domain LOADS (keyword matched) but rules never fire (loaded but useless). ALWAYS_ON domains track rule usage normally. (4) Lesson logged but same mistake recurs 3+ times → rule isn't working, redesign it. (5) Fallback option that works better than primary → swap them. (6) Changelog tracking: rapid rule addition = system forming (normal). Rule removal/modification = system maturing (healthy).
- System pattern retirement rules: (1) Gate STEP (not whole gate) rubber-stamped 20+ times with zero catches → flag step for removal, keep the gate. (2) Smoke check passing 20+ consecutive times → retire to monthly spot-check. (3) CARL LAZY domains: NEVER retire for being dormant — that's their design. Only flag if a domain LOADS (keyword matched) but rules never fire (loaded but useless). ALWAYS_ON domains track rule usage normally. (4) Lesson logged but same mistake recurs 3+ times → rule isn't working, redesign it. (5) Fallback option that works better than primary → swap them. (6) Changelog tracking: rapid rule addition = system forming (normal). Rule removal/modification = system maturing (healthy).
- Every 5 sessions, run a system trend analysis from system-patterns.md: (1) Which audit dimensions are trending down? (2) Which gates are catching real problems vs dead weight? (3) Which lessons graduated vs which are stuck? (4) Are tool failures increasing? (5) Is calibration drift happening? Surface findings to Oliver as "System Loop Report" — 5 lines max.
