- EXPERIMENT PROTOCOL (autoresearch-inspired): (1) ISOLATE — change exactly ONE variable per experiment. Name it explicitly: "subject line length" or "send timing" or "angle for [persona]." Changing two things = two experiments. (2) HYPOTHESIZE — write a 1-line prediction with a numeric threshold BEFORE executing: e.g. "Short subject lines (<5 words) will outperform long (>8 words) by 10%+ reply rate for agency owners." (3) REGISTER — log to brain/system-patterns.md Experiment Log before first send: DATE | EXP-[N] | variable | hypothesis | metric | threshold | STATUS: RUNNING. (4) RUN — execute over one campaign cycle. Minimum 5 data points per variant. Tag every touch with experiment name + variant per LOOP_RULE_3-4. (5) SCORE — binary decision only. KEEP if variant meets or exceeds the threshold. DISCARD if it doesn't. No "interesting but inconclusive" — threshold not met = discard. (6) RECORD — update Experiment Log: STATUS: KEEP [result] or STATUS: DISCARD [result]. KEEP results feed LOOP_RULE_40 (framework effectiveness) as confirmed data. DISCARD results feed PATTERNS.md as negative patterns with [EXPERIMENT] tag. At every 5th session, scan Experiment Log for trends. Maximum 3 concurrent experiments.
- EXPERIMENT PROTOCOL (autoresearch-inspired): (1) ISOLATE — change exactly ONE variable per experiment. Name it explicitly: "subject line length" or "send timing" or "angle for [persona]." Changing two things = two experiments. (2) HYPOTHESIZE — write a 1-line prediction with a numeric threshold BEFORE executing: e.g. "Short subject lines (<5 words) will outperform long (>8 words) by 10%+ reply rate for agency owners." (3) REGISTER — log to brain/system-patterns.md Experiment Log before first send: DATE | EXP-[N] | variable | hypothesis | metric | threshold | STATUS: RUNNING. (4) RUN — execute over one campaign cycle. Minimum 5 data points per variant. Tag every touch with experiment name + variant per LOOP_RULE_3-4. (5) SCORE — binary decision only. KEEP if variant meets or exceeds the threshold. DISCARD if it doesn't. No "interesting but inconclusive" — threshold not met = discard. (6) RECORD — update Experiment Log: STATUS: KEEP [result] or STATUS: DISCARD [result]. KEEP results feed LOOP_RULE_40 (framework effectiveness) as confirmed data. DISCARD results feed PATTERNS.md as negative patterns with [EXPERIMENT] tag. At every 5th session, scan Experiment Log for trends. Maximum 3 concurrent experiments.
- SAME-SESSION TESTING: When a new process rule, gate, or automation is created during a session, it MUST be applied to the NEXT applicable output in that same session. If no applicable output remains, log it as [UNTESTED] in the audit. Rules that aren't tested on creation have zero credibility.
- SAME-SESSION TESTING: When a new process rule, gate, or automation is created during a session, it MUST be applied to the NEXT applicable output in that same session. If no applicable output remains, log it as [UNTESTED] in the audit. Rules that aren't tested on creation have zero credibility.
- CONFIDENCE DECAY: Any pattern in PATTERNS.md older than 90 days without a reinforcing signal (new data point confirming it) automatically steps down one confidence tier. PROVEN → EMERGING. EMERGING → HYPOTHESIS. HYPOTHESIS → INSUFFICIENT. At every session wrap-up where PATTERNS.md is updated, check last_reinforced dates. If any pattern is 90+ days stale, apply the step-down, log to brain/system-patterns.md: "[DATE] DECAY: [pattern] stepped [OLD_TIER] → [NEW_TIER] — no reinforcing signal for [N] days." Decayed patterns can be re-promoted by new data points through normal confidence rules.
- CONFIDENCE DECAY: Any pattern in PATTERNS.md older than 90 days without a reinforcing signal (new data point confirming it) automatically steps down one confidence tier. PROVEN → EMERGING. EMERGING → HYPOTHESIS. HYPOTHESIS → INSUFFICIENT. At every session wrap-up where PATTERNS.md is updated, check last_reinforced dates. If any pattern is 90+ days stale, apply the step-down, log to brain/system-patterns.md: "[DATE] DECAY: [pattern] stepped [OLD_TIER] → [NEW_TIER] — no reinforcing signal for [N] days." Decayed patterns can be re-promoted by new data points through normal confidence rules.
- COLD DATASET FEEDBACK LOOP: Reply and no-reply outcomes from Instantly campaigns feed back into framework auto-selection confidence scores. Reply in cold tier → increment framework confidence for matching persona. No reply across 5+ sends to same persona type → decrement. At wrap-up where Instantly data is reviewed, update cold tier framework scores in PATTERNS.md and log to system-patterns.md.
- COLD DATASET FEEDBACK LOOP: Reply and no-reply outcomes from Instantly campaigns feed back into framework auto-selection confidence scores. Reply in cold tier → increment framework confidence for matching persona. No reply across 5+ sends to same persona type → decrement. At wrap-up where Instantly data is reviewed, update cold tier framework scores in PATTERNS.md and log to system-patterns.md.
- CARL COMPACTION PROTOCOL: When total CARL behavioral rule count approaches 100, trigger a compaction review. COUNTING METHOD: Only count rules in behavioral domains (loop, agents, coldcall, context, demo-prep, global, linkedin, listbuild, prospect-email). EXCLUDE .carl/commands (star-command shortcuts) and .carl/example-custom-domain (template file) — these are NOT behavioral rules and do not count toward the ceiling. Report format always: "Behavioral rules: [N] / 100 ceiling [status] | loop: [N] | [domain]: [N] | ... | Star-commands: [N] (excluded) | Templates: [N] (excluded)". Identify compaction candidates: (a) hasn't fired in 20 sessions, (b) overlaps >50% with another rule, (c) specific instance of a general rule, (d) written by learning loop >60 days ago and never Oliver-confirmed. Propose merges and graduations. Oliver approves all changes. Log to system-evolution.md. HARD FLOOR: never below 40 rules. Target distribution: Tier 1 hard constraints (10-15), Tier 2 process (20-30), Tier 3 learning (15-20), Tier 4 domain (10-15) = 55-80 total.
- CARL COMPACTION PROTOCOL: When total CARL behavioral rule count approaches 100, trigger a compaction review. COUNTING METHOD: Only count rules in behavioral domains (loop, agents, coldcall, context, demo-prep, global, linkedin, listbuild, prospect-email). EXCLUDE .carl/commands (star-command shortcuts) and .carl/example-custom-domain (template file) — these are NOT behavioral rules and do not count toward the ceiling. Report format always: "Behavioral rules: [N] / 100 ceiling [status] | loop: [N] | [domain]: [N] | ... | Star-commands: [N] (excluded) | Templates: [N] (excluded)". Identify compaction candidates: (a) hasn't fired in 20 sessions, (b) overlaps >50% with another rule, (c) specific instance of a general rule, (d) written by learning loop >60 days ago and never Oliver-confirmed. Propose merges and graduations. Oliver approves all changes. Log to system-evolution.md. HARD FLOOR: never below 40 rules. Target distribution: Tier 1 hard constraints (10-15), Tier 2 process (20-30), Tier 3 learning (15-20), Tier 4 domain (10-15) = 55-80 total.
- VAULT DECAY — PROSPECT NOTES: At wrap-up step 7, check brain/prospects/ for notes older than 90 days (last_touch or file modification) with no active Pipedrive deal. Move to brain/archive/prospects/. Log: "[DATE] VAULT DECAY: [prospect] archived — [N] days, no active deal." Archived notes remain in PATTERNS.md aggregates permanently — only the file moves.
- VAULT DECAY — PROSPECT NOTES: At wrap-up step 7, check brain/prospects/ for notes older than 90 days (last_touch or file modification) with no active Pipedrive deal. Move to brain/archive/prospects/. Log: "[DATE] VAULT DECAY: [prospect] archived — [N] days, no active deal." Archived notes remain in PATTERNS.md aggregates permanently — only the file moves.
- VAULT DECAY — PERSONA CONFIDENCE: At wrap-up step 7, check brain/personas/ for pattern entries with no reinforcing signal in 60 days. Step down one confidence tier per decay rules. Log to system-patterns.md. New interactions re-promote through normal confidence rules.
- VAULT DECAY — PERSONA CONFIDENCE: At wrap-up step 7, check brain/personas/ for pattern entries with no reinforcing signal in 60 days. Step down one confidence tier per decay rules. Log to system-patterns.md. New interactions re-promote through normal confidence rules.
- MICRO-REFLECTION TRIGGER: Every time something new is added to the system (CARL rule, lesson, gate step, file, hook), run a 60-second reflection BEFORE committing: (1) Does this conflict with anything existing? (2) Does this make any existing rule redundant? If yes, propose removing it in the same commit. (3) Does this unlock any new capability? Log to .claude/micro-reflections.md. If a conflict IS found, resolve before adding. If a redundancy IS found, remove in the same change.
