- After post-enrichment scoring (Step 4), scan each surviving lead's company_domain for ad platform signals (Meta Pixel, Google Ads tag, GTM, Klaviyo, Shopify). This is FREE (website fetch only, no API credits). Add columns: meta_pixel, google_ads, ad_platforms, likely_budget_tier, top_roas_gap. Use domain/reference/meta-api-patterns.md and domain/reference/google-ads-patterns.md inference tables. If domain missing or scan fails, infer from industry + company_size. These columns power personalized cold email angles and demo prep. See lead-filtering-sop.md Step 4b for full detection spec.
- Instantly cold outreach data is tracked in PATTERNS.md under the COLD TIER. When Oliver says "pull data from Instantly" or "check campaign performance", query Instantly MCP tools, update the cold tier tables. Key insight: Anna's campaigns provide volume data (what angles/personas work at scale), Oliver's pipeline provides precision data (what converts to revenue). Both feed Loop.
- Instantly cold outreach data is tracked in PATTERNS.md under the COLD TIER. When Oliver says "pull data from Instantly" or "check campaign performance", query Instantly MCP tools, update the cold tier tables. Key insight: Anna's campaigns provide volume data (what angles/personas work at scale), Oliver's pipeline provides precision data (what converts to revenue). Both feed Loop.
- Key Instantly insights baked into Loop (from 82K+ emails): (1) Break-up email (Step 4) is the highest-reply touch. (2) Founder-to-founder framing gets warmer responses. (3) Research/curiosity angle generates most pipeline volume. (4) Pattern interrupt on Step 2 triggers curiosity replies. (5) Agency vertical is the best-performing segment (8.8% reply). (6) "Replace your agency" is dead (0.1%). (7) Short subject lines outperform.
- Key Instantly insights baked into Loop (from 82K+ emails): (1) Break-up email (Step 4) is the highest-reply touch. (2) Founder-to-founder framing gets warmer responses. (3) Research/curiosity angle generates most pipeline volume. (4) Pattern interrupt on Step 2 triggers curiosity replies. (5) Agency vertical is the best-performing segment (8.8% reply). (6) "Replace your agency" is dead (0.1%). (7) Short subject lines outperform.
- Auditor → Gates. When post-session audit scores a dimension below 7, check if a gate covers that dimension. If yes, tighten the gate step (add a check, raise the bar). If no gate covers it, flag for new gate step creation. Track: auditor_to_gate_fires, improvements_made.
- Auditor → Gates. When post-session audit scores a dimension below 7, check if a gate covers that dimension. If yes, tighten the gate step (add a check, raise the bar). If no gate covers it, flag for new gate step creation. Track: auditor_to_gate_fires, improvements_made.
- Gates → Lessons. When a gate catches a real problem (not rubber-stamped), auto-generate a lesson in lessons.md if the problem pattern isn't already captured. Format: "[DATE] GATE-GENERATED: [gate name] caught [problem] → [rule]". Track: gate_to_lesson_fires, lessons_generated.
- Gates → Lessons. When a gate catches a real problem (not rubber-stamped), auto-generate a lesson in lessons.md if the problem pattern isn't already captured. Format: "[DATE] GATE-GENERATED: [gate name] caught [problem] → [rule]". Track: gate_to_lesson_fires, lessons_generated.
- Lessons → CARL Rules. When a lesson has prevented the same mistake 3+ times (tracked in system-patterns.md Lesson Effectiveness table), promote it to a CARL rule in the appropriate domain. Remove from lessons.md, add to domain file with comment "# Graduated from lesson [date]". Track: lesson_to_carl_fires, rules_created.
- Lessons → CARL Rules. When a lesson has prevented the same mistake 3+ times (tracked in system-patterns.md Lesson Effectiveness table), promote it to a CARL rule in the appropriate domain. Remove from lessons.md, add to domain file with comment "# Graduated from lesson [date]". Track: lesson_to_carl_fires, rules_created.
- Smoke Failures → Auto-Lessons. When any smoke check fails (thread matching, email format, deal ID, etc.), auto-generate a lesson if one doesn't already exist for that failure mode. The lesson includes the fix. Track: smoke_to_lesson_fires, lessons_generated.
- Smoke Failures → Auto-Lessons. When any smoke check fails (thread matching, email format, deal ID, etc.), auto-generate a lesson if one doesn't already exist for that failure mode. The lesson includes the fix. Track: smoke_to_lesson_fires, lessons_generated.
- Rubric Drift → Auto-Tighten. When Oliver corrects a self-score by 2+ points on the same output type 3 times, auto-tighten that rubric dimension by 1 point in quality-rubrics.md. Track: drift_corrections, rubrics_tightened.
- Rubric Drift → Auto-Tighten. When Oliver corrects a self-score by 2+ points on the same output type 3 times, auto-tighten that rubric dimension by 1 point in quality-rubrics.md. Track: drift_corrections, rubrics_tightened.
- Fallback Success → Auto-Reorder. When a fallback tool works on first try 5+ times while the primary fails, swap primary and fallback in fallback-chains.md. Track: reorder_fires, swaps_made.
- Fallback Success → Auto-Reorder. When a fallback tool works on first try 5+ times while the primary fails, swap primary and fallback in fallback-chains.md. Track: reorder_fires, swaps_made.
- PATTERNS.md → Gates. When PATTERNS.md shows an angle with [PROVEN] failure rate >80% for a persona, add it to the Pre-Draft gate as a blocked angle for that persona. Prevent wasting touches on dead approaches. Track: pattern_to_gate_fires, angles_blocked.
