- EVENT CONNECTION TRACKING: Every event connection (hooks + rules 28-34) has tracking counters: fires (times triggered), value_produced (times output was useful — used by Oliver, prevented a mistake, improved a score). Update at wrap-up step 9 in system-patterns.md Event Connection Performance table. Health scoring: value_rate = value_produced / fires. Below 0.2 after 10+ fires → LOW VALUE, flag for review. Above 0.6 → HIGH VALUE, consider strengthening. Zero fires after 5 sessions → DORMANT, investigate.
- EVENT CONNECTION TRACKING: Every event connection (hooks + rules 28-34) has tracking counters: fires (times triggered), value_produced (times output was useful — used by Oliver, prevented a mistake, improved a score). Update at wrap-up step 9 in system-patterns.md Event Connection Performance table. Health scoring: value_rate = value_produced / fires. Below 0.2 after 10+ fires → LOW VALUE, flag for review. Above 0.6 → HIGH VALUE, consider strengthening. Zero fires after 5 sessions → DORMANT, investigate.
- META-LOOP OPERATION: Runs every 5th session (aligned with system trend analysis). Produces "Connection Report" — 3 lines max: (1) highest-value event connection and why, (2) lowest-value connection and recommendation (tighten, loosen, or kill), (3) dormant connections to investigate. Self-tracking: after 3 meta-loop cycles (15 sessions), evaluate if recommendations improved system performance. No improvement → simplify to annual review. RECURSION CAP: maximum 3 layers (L1 sales, L2 system, L3 meta). No Layer 4. Complexity earns its keep or dies.
- META-LOOP OPERATION: Runs every 5th session (aligned with system trend analysis). Produces "Connection Report" — 3 lines max: (1) highest-value event connection and why, (2) lowest-value connection and recommendation (tighten, loosen, or kill), (3) dormant connections to investigate. Self-tracking: after 3 meta-loop cycles (15 sessions), evaluate if recommendations improved system performance. No improvement → simplify to annual review. RECURSION CAP: maximum 3 layers (L1 sales, L2 system, L3 meta). No Layer 4. Complexity earns its keep or dies.
- CONVERGENCE & KILL SWITCHES: Kill switch: every optimization mechanism has a cycle counter. 5 consecutive cycles producing zero actionable changes → auto-disable to DORMANT. Oliver can re-enable. Convergence detection: system is converging when (a) audit scores 9+ for 3 sessions, (b) no new lessons for 3 sessions, (c) CARL rules stable for 3 sessions, (d) event connection value rates above 0.5 or dormant. When converging → reduce meta-loop to every 10 sessions. Maturity indicators tracked in system-patterns.md: sessions_since_last_new_lesson, sessions_since_last_rule_change, sessions_since_last_gate_catch, avg_audit_score_last_5, event_connection_dormancy_rate. 4/5 stable → system is mature.
- CONVERGENCE & KILL SWITCHES: Kill switch: every optimization mechanism has a cycle counter. 5 consecutive cycles producing zero actionable changes → auto-disable to DORMANT. Oliver can re-enable. Convergence detection: system is converging when (a) audit scores 9+ for 3 sessions, (b) no new lessons for 3 sessions, (c) CARL rules stable for 3 sessions, (d) event connection value rates above 0.5 or dormant. When converging → reduce meta-loop to every 10 sessions. Maturity indicators tracked in system-patterns.md: sessions_since_last_new_lesson, sessions_since_last_rule_change, sessions_since_last_gate_catch, avg_audit_score_last_5, event_connection_dormancy_rate. 4/5 stable → system is mature.
- DIVERGENCE & COMPLEXITY BUDGET: Divergence: if a converged system shows audit score below 8, 3+ new lessons in one session, or 2+ smoke check failures → re-enable dormant optimizations, increase meta-loop to every 5 sessions. Complexity budget: max 10 event connections, max 5 meta-loop trackers, max 100 CARL behavioral rules. At 90% of any limit → trigger pruning, remove lowest value_rate first. Complexity is a finite resource.
- DIVERGENCE & COMPLEXITY BUDGET: Divergence: if a converged system shows audit score below 8, 3+ new lessons in one session, or 2+ smoke check failures → re-enable dormant optimizations, increase meta-loop to every 5 sessions. Complexity budget: max 10 event connections, max 5 meta-loop trackers, max 100 CARL behavioral rules. At 90% of any limit → trigger pruning, remove lowest value_rate first. Complexity is a finite resource.
- DEAL HEALTH & CLOSE PROBABILITY: Health score (0-100) per active deal from: (a) days_in_stage vs avg, (b) touches_without_reply vs avg, (c) last_touch_recency, (d) objection_severity (none=1.0, soft=0.8, hard=0.6, budget=0.4), (e) engagement_signals (replied=+0.2, questions=+0.1, meeting=+0.3). Below 40 = AT RISK, surface proactively at startup for deals not already flagged overdue. Requires 10+ closed deals to calibrate; until then tag [UNCALIBRATED]. Close probability (15+ deals): probability = base_rate × stage_multiplier × recency × engagement. Weighted pipeline = sum(probability × deal_value). Until calibrated, note "[NEEDS 15+ CLOSED DEALS]".
- DEAL HEALTH & CLOSE PROBABILITY: Health score (0-100) per active deal from: (a) days_in_stage vs avg, (b) touches_without_reply vs avg, (c) last_touch_recency, (d) objection_severity (none=1.0, soft=0.8, hard=0.6, budget=0.4), (e) engagement_signals (replied=+0.2, questions=+0.1, meeting=+0.3). Below 40 = AT RISK, surface proactively at startup for deals not already flagged overdue. Requires 10+ closed deals to calibrate; until then tag [UNCALIBRATED]. Close probability (15+ deals): probability = base_rate × stage_multiplier × recency × engagement. Weighted pipeline = sum(probability × deal_value). Until calibrated, note "[NEEDS 15+ CLOSED DEALS]".
- FRAMEWORK EFFECTIVENESS: Track per framework (CCQ, Gap Selling, JOLT, SPIN, Challenger): times_used, conversion_rate_by_persona, avg_deal_velocity. Every 5 sessions compare. Below 10% conversion after 10+ uses → flag for archival. Above 40% for a persona → auto-tag as DEFAULT in PATTERNS.md. Auto-update triggers: demo thread order closes faster → update defaults; tone+angle combo outperforms 2x → add as recommended; follow-up timing outperforms → override cadence. Dead detection: framework file not loaded in 20+ sessions AND no PATTERNS.md data → archive. Oliver confirms before deletion.
- FRAMEWORK EFFECTIVENESS: Track per framework (CCQ, Gap Selling, JOLT, SPIN, Challenger): times_used, conversion_rate_by_persona, avg_deal_velocity. Every 5 sessions compare. Below 10% conversion after 10+ uses → flag for archival. Above 40% for a persona → auto-tag as DEFAULT in PATTERNS.md. Auto-update triggers: demo thread order closes faster → update defaults; tone+angle combo outperforms 2x → add as recommended; follow-up timing outperforms → override cadence. Dead detection: framework file not loaded in 20+ sessions AND no PATTERNS.md data → archive. Oliver confirms before deletion.
- SIGNAL MONITORING: Signal types in brain/signals.md: TRIGGER (funding, new role, expansion), INTENT (pricing page visit, demo request), COMPETITIVE (evaluating alternatives), SOCIAL (LinkedIn post about pain), MARKET (industry news). Each signal: source, prospect, date_detected, relevance_score, action_taken. At startup, scan for unprocessed signals — relevance > 7 gets immediate attention, others queue for next touch. Sources: Gmail auto-forwards from Google Alerts, Apollo job change alerts, Instantly reply sentiment, Calendly booking notifications.
- SIGNAL MONITORING: Signal types in brain/signals.md: TRIGGER (funding, new role, expansion), INTENT (pricing page visit, demo request), COMPETITIVE (evaluating alternatives), SOCIAL (LinkedIn post about pain), MARKET (industry news). Each signal: source, prospect, date_detected, relevance_score, action_taken. At startup, scan for unprocessed signals — relevance > 7 gets immediate attention, others queue for next touch. Sources: Gmail auto-forwards from Google Alerts, Apollo job change alerts, Instantly reply sentiment, Calendly booking notifications.
- DORMANCY RE-EVALUATION TRIGGER: Event connections in DORMANT status get a mandatory review pass when ANY of these structural changes occur: (1) CLAUDE.md is modified, (2) a new tool is added, (3) a new hook is created, (4) a CARL domain is significantly modified. Check each dormant connection: given the structural change, is the trigger condition now more likely to fire? If yes, move back to ACTIVE with note in audit-log.md.
- DORMANCY RE-EVALUATION TRIGGER: Event connections in DORMANT status get a mandatory review pass when ANY of these structural changes occur: (1) CLAUDE.md is modified, (2) a new tool is added, (3) a new hook is created, (4) a CARL domain is significantly modified. Check each dormant connection: given the structural change, is the trigger condition now more likely to fire? If yes, move back to ACTIVE with note in audit-log.md.
- CONVERGENCE CAPABILITY REVIEW: When all 5 convergence indicators (LOOP_RULE_37) are stable, produce a capability gap analysis: (1) STRENGTHS: what the system handles well, (2) MANUAL GAPS: activities still handled manually, (3) CAPABILITY EXPANSIONS: 3 suggestions ranked by leverage. Write to .claude/review-queue.md. Only generate once per convergence event.
- CONVERGENCE CAPABILITY REVIEW: When all 5 convergence indicators (LOOP_RULE_37) are stable, produce a capability gap analysis: (1) STRENGTHS: what the system handles well, (2) MANUAL GAPS: activities still handled manually, (3) CAPABILITY EXPANSIONS: 3 suggestions ranked by leverage. Write to .claude/review-queue.md. Only generate once per convergence event.
- DATA COMPACTION: At wrap-up step 7 (anti-bloat), run compaction on PATTERNS.md: (1) Angles with identical persona + similar reply rates (within 5%) merge into one entry with combined sample size. (2) Framework effectiveness entries unchanged for 10+ sessions compress to one-line summaries. (3) Cross-Deal Insights older than 60 days without reinforcement archive to "Historical Insights." (4) Cadence data matching the default (LOOP_RULE_11) exactly gets removed — only overrides persist. Goal: PATTERNS.md stays under 300 lines.
