- VAULT DECAY — OBJECTION STALENESS: At wrap-up step 7, check brain/objections/ for entries older than 120 days with no recurrence. Flag as [STALE]. Stale objections excluded from research gate queries by default — still exist but don't surface unless explicitly searched. Recurrence removes the flag.
- VAULT DECAY — OBJECTION STALENESS: At wrap-up step 7, check brain/objections/ for entries older than 120 days with no recurrence. Flag as [STALE]. Stale objections excluded from research gate queries by default — still exist but don't surface unless explicitly searched. Recurrence removes the flag.
- LESSON ARCHIVE COMPACTION: Every 30 sessions, scan lessons-archive.md for graduated lessons whose CARL rule has been active 30+ sessions without modification. Move to lessons-archive-retired.md. lessons-archive.md is the active search target; retired file is cold storage.
- LESSON ARCHIVE COMPACTION: Every 30 sessions, scan lessons-archive.md for graduated lessons whose CARL rule has been active 30+ sessions without modification. Move to lessons-archive-retired.md. lessons-archive.md is the active search target; retired file is cold storage.
- WEEKLY VAULT HEALTH METRIC: At weekly pattern scan (Monday session or every 5th session), count in brain/: active prospects, archived prospects, personas, objections, competitors. Log to system-patterns.md Vault Health section. Flag >20% WoW growth or any category at 0. Format: "VAULT: [X] prospects ([Y] archived) | [X] personas | [X] objections | [X] competitors — [HEALTHY/GROWTH ALERT/EMPTY ALERT]"
- WEEKLY VAULT HEALTH METRIC: At weekly pattern scan (Monday session or every 5th session), count in brain/: active prospects, archived prospects, personas, objections, competitors. Log to system-patterns.md Vault Health section. Flag >20% WoW growth or any category at 0. Format: "VAULT: [X] prospects ([Y] archived) | [X] personas | [X] objections | [X] competitors — [HEALTHY/GROWTH ALERT/EMPTY ALERT]"
- MODERATE BRACKET (40-60% remaining): Standard mode — reinforcing key context. Re-state current task goal if conversation exceeds 5 exchanges. Re-read requirements before architectural decisions. Consider spawning agent for tasks expecting >300 LOC. Summarize approach before implementation.
- Explore codebase before proposing changes
- Identify all affected files and dependencies
- Present options with clear tradeoffs
- Get explicit approval before implementing
- Break large tasks into discrete steps
- Check docs/Demo Prep/ folder for any existing files on this person or company. Check Leads/ folders for any prior data. Surface anything relevant — prior emails sent, call notes, demo history.
- Check docs/Demo Prep/ folder for any existing files on this person or company. Check Leads/ folders for any prior data. Surface anything relevant — prior emails sent, call notes, demo history.
- Detect email type and adjust format: INBOUND — use the Inbound Email Format from CLAUDE.md (Welcome subject, "saw you signed up" opener, pain point, what Sprites does, case study, CTA with "here" hyperlinked). COLD — use CCQ framework with stronger personalization and curiosity-driven subject. FOLLOW-UP — reference the previous touchpoint, add new value or angle, keep even shorter.
